verses.roman:
'jagannātha-vallabha' nāma udyāna-pradhāne
praveśa karilā prabhu lañā bhakta-gaṇe

synonyms: jagannātha-vallabha—Jagannātha-vallabha; nāma—named; udyāna-pradhāne—one of the best gardens; praveśa karilā—entered; prabhu—Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; lañā—taking; bhakta-gaṇe—the devotees.
translation: The Lord, along with His devotees, entered one of the nicest gardens, called Jagannātha-vallabha.
